Jaguar cubs born at Elmwood Park Zoo Updated: January 31, 2017 — 8:06 AM EST 295 Share Emily Babay Staff Writer 
Emily Babay is a breaking news producer. She writes about everything from crime to transit problems — and occasionally about good news. More by Emily Babay 
The Elmwood Park Zoo's jaguar exhibit just doubled in size. 
Inka, the Norristown zoo's female jaguar, gave birth on Jan. 24 to two cubs, officials said Tuesday.
